    comment: '<p>The HTML input form <code>type="password"</code> attribute is used to display each character either as an asterisk, or a circle. This attribute is very similar to the <code>type="text"</code> attribute, but hides each character entered.</p>\n<p>Example:</p>\n<pre><code class="language-html">&#x3C;form\n  action="/action.php">\n  Username:\n  &#x3C;input\n    type="text"\n    name="username">\n  Password:\n  &#x3C;input\n    type="password"\n    name="password">\n  &#x3C;input\n    type="submit"\n    value="Submit">\n&#x3C;/form>\n</code></pre>\n<p><svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="320" height="154"><g fill="none" fill-rule="evenodd"><rect width="320" height="154" fill="#FFF" rx="9"/><text fill="#000" font-family="ArialMT, Arial" font-size="14"><tspan x="20" y="30">Username: </tspan></text><text fill="#000" font-family="ArialMT, Arial" font-size="14"><tspan x="20" y="80">Password: </tspan></text><path fill="#FFF" stroke="#CCC" d="M20.5 90.5h130v18h-130z"/><text fill="#000" font-family="ArialMT, Arial" font-size="10"><tspan x="25" y="104">●●●●●●●●●●●</tspan></text><path fill="#FFF" stroke="#CCC" d="M20.5 40.5h130v18h-130z"/><text fill="#000" font-family="ArialMT, Arial" font-size="14"><tspan x="24" y="55">admin</tspan></text><rect width="52" height="17" x="20.5" y="116.5" stroke="#D3D3D3" rx="4"/><text fill="#000" font-family="ArialMT, Arial" font-size="14"><tspan x="20" y="30">Username: </tspan></text><text fill="#000" font-family="Arial-BoldMT, Arial" font-size="11.5" font-weight="bold"><tspan x="27" y="129">Submit</tspan></text></g></svg></p>\n<!--[View CodePen](https://codepen.io/enkidevs/pen/dKwgVW)--> \n<p>Where the Username field accepts text as normal, the Password field hides the characters typed by displaying them as bullets (•••)</p>\n',
